title: Mudanças no navegador Mozilla
content:
Prezados,

Alguns dias o meu Mozilla apresenta falhas ao iniciar, principalmente em sites. Não estou conseguindo acessar quase nenhuma site dos favoritos. Também, depois de iniciar o navegador ele começou ser exibido em idioma inglês e sem minhas personalizações tipo skins e outros , o modo escuro por exemplo. Para o navegador voltar como eu gosto, preciso ajustar tudo novamente e ao desligar o computador a personalização do Firefox também está sendo resetada. Não estão aparecendo os ícones das extensões também. Comunico, que não mexi nas configurações, nem as pessoas terceiras tem acesso ao meu laptop. Anexo o print como que aparece o meu navegador, observem a cor clara (uso sempre modo escuro) e falta dos ícones das extensões do Metamask, Kaspersky (uso antivírus Kaspersky), Privacy Badget e outros.

title: firefox won't restore after win 7 crash
content:
Hi,

I have the following problem: Windows 7 crashed after coming back from standby. When I restarted Firefox it restored a 3-month-old session. The sessionstore.jsonlz4 file was missing in the profile folder. I searched for a backup in the sessionstore-backups folder; unfortunately all were too old. Windows Restore was not running on my computer.

Using EaseUS Data Recovery I found a recovery.baklz4 file from 10 days ago, tried renaming it etc. but Firefox won't use it for recovering. It is probably corrupt ...

I used https://www.jeffersonscher.com/ffu/scrounger.html but I get an error saying: Session history file contents could not be read?

Is there any way to repair the file or extract the URLs to use them manually?

Or any other solution is very welcome! Thank you very much!

title: Running performace profiler might cause massive graphical artifacts
content:
There is a chance that when I use the performance profiler for GPU-related tasks, Firefox becomes unstable and renders content incorrectly. Videos and GPU-intensive tasks, may not display properly or might flash intermittently, and everything graphic like icons and CSS elements gets replaced by other assets.

I've encountered this problem twice, and both times it occurred after I used the performance profiler. My GPU is neither overclocked nor overheated, and 3D and other GPU tasks in different programs work fine.

Reopening Firefox fixes the issue.

I don't know how to reproduce the problem consistently, but I have noticed that if the Firefox window flashes to black when I start the profiler, the issue is likely to occur.

Specs: GPU: GTX 1060 6GB CPU: i5-7500 RAM: 32GB
creator: neurs

title: Restart after update fails every time
content:
I've put up with this issue for about a year now. Every time FF updates, the "restart" fails. It reopens the browser, and if you had multiple tabs open all of them are also opened - all at the same time.

I've tried to go through the process with just 1 tab and it fails. I wait 2 or 3 minutes for the page to resolve and it never does. So I have to close FF manually and reopen FF before it will function normally again. It's not a huge issue, but it's very important when I'm in the midst of working with several tabs open in the middle of the day. I've learned to "not" close and allow FF to update when I'm working with a lot of tabs. I wait until the end of the day to close FF because it can be a 10 minute disruption to my work (which actually becomes 30 minutes by the time I can get back to what I was doing after opening all the tabs I needed open).

With every update I think, "this time" the FF restart will be fixed....but it's not. I just went through it this morning when I opened FF. I know it downloaded and updated yesterday at the end of my day, which means I shut down FF and my other windows, but I always leave my computer running 24/7, and then turn off my monitors.

When I opened FF today, it attempted to load the 1 tab I had open last night, and after several minutes I simply closed FF and started again. It's that "second" restart that gets everything functioning in FF.

Certainly others have complained about this. I can't be the only person with this issue. Is this just something that's not easy to figure out "why" it won't connect to the Net on restart? That's the issue, actually. FF loses the connection to the Net during the update process and when the restart happens FF can't connect to the Net. Only a manual restart fixes the issue.

title: Textdarstellung auf immer mehr Webseiten in Firefox falsch!!!
content:
Auf immer mehr Webseiten erhalten wir mit Firefox (jeweils aktuellste Version) zunehmend falsche Textdarstellung! Es herrscht Durcheinander im Text, Worte fehlen, falsche Worte erscheinen (vermischte)

Dies ist ein reines Firefox-Problem. EDGE oder CHROME zeigen die entsprechenden Seiten fehlerfrei an. Insofern kann auch die Rechner-/Betriebssystem-Konfiguration nicht die Ursachen sein.

Es liegt auch offenbar nicht an den Sicherheitseinstellungen von Firefox, die wurden bereits aktiviert/deaktiviert wie in allen Hilfstexten vorgeschlagen.

title: Firefox always asks which profile to start, ignoring command line arguments
content:
Hi, I'm not sure if this is a bug, or me not using FF properly.

I want Firefox in general to ask me, which profile to use when started. So in the Profile-Manager, I removed the checkbox for "Use selected profile without asking as startup".

Now, I wanted to create a shortcut for a specific profile, so I tried running `firefox -P "myProfile"` or even `firefox -p "/path/to/myProfile"`. In both cases I get the window asking me which profile to use.

Debian 12.6 - SwayWM Firefox 128.0 (64-bit)

title: Firefox update process doesn’t launch by itself after closing Firefox for update anymore on macOS Monterey
content:
For the last few weeks, I have had the following issue on macOS Monterey (version 12.7.5) on Apple M1:

When I choose the “Restart now” option in the “Update ready to install” dialog, Firefox closes and I type the password at the admin prompt, but then nothing else happens. The Mozilla Updater process won’t appear in the Activity Monitor, and if I click on the Firefox icon in the Dock, another admin prompt appears, then the updater actually does its thing but at the same time the old version of Firefox tries to launch during the updating process. Sometimes, the updated version of Firefox appears while the old version is also on the screen. It is a really janky process and I always fear that something gets severely broken.

This never happened on macOS Big Sur, the previous major version of macOS.

title: Firefox
content: Dobrý den. Omlouvám se, nejde mi o dotaz, ale chci sdělit výsledek snahy o obnovení Firefoxu. Předevčírem jsem prosila o pomoc. Firefox mi přestal fungovat. Několikrát jsem restartovala, ale všechny pokusy byly marné. Žádala jsem pomoc i od podpory, dostala jsem na výběr několik možností, ale nic mi nepomohlo. Včera jsem ještě jednou restartovala a po kliknutí na ikonu Firefoxu na obrazovce konečně program naskočil (předtím to nešlo). Dřív mi vždycky ikona naskočila na dolní lištu, ale hlavně že teď Firefox normálně funguje. Od podpory jsem dostala pokyn, že mám informovat, když dostanu odpověď na vlákno (možná píši nesmysl), ale stránka, na které bych byla měla pokračovat, se mi ztratila při restartu. Tak jako tak chci poděkovat za pomoc a za trpělivost a přeji hodně radosti a pěkné léto.
